      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Switching to generator functions is a fantastic idea for tackling massive data, as they process data lazily, which is much more memory-efficient than loading everything into memory at once like a list comprehension would. If your memory error is happening because the entire dataset is being loaded into memory simultaneously, generators will help by yielding one item at a time. You might also consider using chunking when reading the CSV with pandas, which is a dedicated technique for handling files too large for RAM. These methods, combined, should significantly reduce your memory footprint.",
